-- ANZ Hires Fiona Ju as Director of Loan Syndications for China
-- B y   W e n d y   M o c k
-- 2012-04-30T10:08:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-30/anz-hires-fiona-ju-as-director-of-loan-syndications-for-china.html
Australia & New Zealand Banking
Group Ltd. (ANZ)  hired Fiona Ju as director of loan syndications in
Beijing, according to the Melbourne-based bank.  “Ju will be driving our debt origination in China,
initially focusing on state-owned enterprise related
companies,” John Corrin, ANZ’s global head of loan syndications
based in Hong Kong, said by telephone today. Her first day in
the new position will be May 2, Corrin said.  Ju was previously a director of structured finance based in
Beijing with BNP Paribas SA, according to Corrin.  Brenda Woo, a Hong Kong-based spokeswoman for BNP Paribas,
declined to immediately comment when asked about Ju’s move today
by telephone.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Wendy Mock in Hong Kong at 
